# 6. Content Hierarchy Rules

The SFC hierarchy follows these rules:

---

# Rule 1 — Parent / Child Visibility

A child object may have:

* the same visibility as its parent,
* higher visibility than its parent.

A child may never have lower visibility.

---

## Visibility Ranking

Highest visibility:

```text
Public
```

↓

```text
Restricted
```

↓

```text
Private
```

---

## Valid Example

```text
Series:

Restricted


Season:

Restricted


Episode:

Public
```

The Episode can be publicly accessible.

---

## Invalid Example

```text
Series:

Public


Season:

Restricted
```

The Season cannot reduce visibility below its parent.

---

# Rule 2 — Published Content Requirement

A content object is only discoverable when it contains meaningful published content.

Requirements:

---

## Channel

Requires:

```text
At least one published Page
```

through its content hierarchy.

---

## Series

Requires:

```text
At least one published Page
```

---

## Season

Requires:

```text
At least one published Page
```

---

## Episode

Requires:

```text
Page 1 exists

AND

Page 1 is published
```

---

# Rule 3 — Empty Structures Are Allowed

Creators may create incomplete structures.

Examples:

Valid:

```text
Channel

    New Series

        No Episodes Yet
```

Invalid:

```text
Publish Series
```

because it contains no published story.

