# 7. Ownership Model

---

# 7.1 Ownership Principle

Ownership and public identity are separate concepts.

The Creator owns content.

The Channel publishes content.

---

# 7.2 MVP Ownership

MVP:

```text
User Account

    owns

Creator Identity

    owns

Channel

    owns

Content
```

---

# 7.3 Future Collaboration Model

Future versions may introduce:

* collaborators,
* roles,
* organizations,
* classrooms,
* project teams.

Possible roles:

```text
Owner

Editor

Contributor

Reviewer

Viewer
```

---

# 7.4 Channel Transfer

Channel ownership transfer is supported.

Possible future scenarios:

* organization ownership,
* project transfer,
* creator retirement,
* acquisition.

---

# 8. Visibility Model

---

# 8.1 Purpose

Visibility controls who may discover and access content.

---

# 8.2 Visibility Levels

## Public

Accessible by everyone.

Content is:

* searchable,
* viewable,
* shareable.

---

## Restricted

Visible to the public as an existing object.

Access requires permission.

Examples:

* paid content,
* groups,
* classrooms.

---

## Private

Not publicly visible.

Accessible only to authorized users.

Examples:

* family sharing,
* private projects.

---

# 8.3 Future Access Models

Future versions may support:

* subscriptions,
* memberships,
* classroom access,
* organizations,
* fan groups.

---

# 9. Lifecycle Model

---

# 9.1 Channel Lifecycle

```text
Active
 |
 |
Archived
 |
 |
Deleted
```

---

## Active

Normal operation.

---

## Archived

No longer actively promoted.

Still recoverable.

---

## Deleted

Removed after explicit request.

Not an immediate action.

---

# 9.2 Episode Lifecycle

MVP:

```text
Draft

Published

Deleted
```

---

## Draft

Creator editing state.

Not visible publicly.

---

## Published

Available according to visibility settings.

---

## Deleted

Removed from normal viewing.

Recoverable according to deletion rules.

---

# 10. Publishing Model

---

# 10.1 Publishing Principle

Publishing makes creator content available to viewers according to visibility rules.

---

# 10.2 Publishing Workflow

General workflow:

```text
Create

↓

Edit

↓

Preview

↓

Publish
```

---

# 10.3 Preview

Before publishing:

Creators may preview:

* Pages,
* Episodes,
* Playback behavior.

Deleted Pages are excluded from preview.

---

# 10.4 Published Editing

Published content remains editable.

Workflow:

```text
Published Content

↓

Create Revision

↓

Edit

↓

Preview

↓

Publish Revision

↓

Replace Published Version
```

---

# 10.5 Revision History

MVP:

No full revision history.

Publishing a revision replaces the previous published version.

---

# 11. Playback Model

---

# 11.1 Purpose

Playback presents the creator's intended storytelling experience.

---

# 11.2 Playback Modes

## Episode Playback

Plays:

```text
Episode

Page 1

Page 2

Page 3

...
```

automatically.

---

## Page Playback

Starts playback from the current Page.

Acts as a resume point.

---

## Component Playback

Viewer selects an individual component.

Example:

Click:

* image,
* video,
* animation.

---

# 11.3 Canvas Model

SFC uses a responsive Canvas model.

---

## Creator View

Creator designs using:

* chosen orientation,
* defined dimensions,
* component placement.

---

## Viewer View

The Canvas:

* scales to device size,
* preserves proportions,
* supports zoom.

---

## Device Support

Designed for:

* desktop,
* tablet,
* mobile.

---

